description:
This dataset contains soil physicochemical properties and functional gene abundances (qPCR) from four long-term organic amendment field trial sites in Kenya (Aludeka, Embu, Machanga, Sidada), collected in 2021. Variables include ammonium, nitrate, bulk density, total organic carbon, total nitrogen, C:N ratio, soil texture (clay/silt/sand), pH, and copy numbers for seven functional genes (16S, AOA, AOB, nifH, nirK, nirS, nosZI). Samples span four organic amendment treatments (CT, FYM, MS, TD) crossed with two nitrogen input levels (+N, &minus;N), replicated across all sites. 
 Amplicon sequencing data (16S rRNA and ITS) generated from the same samples are deposited at the European Nucleotide Archive under accession  PRJEB103795 , following standard open-access practice for sequence data.&nbsp; 
 Supporting data for: Visscher AM, Ndungu SM, Feola Conz R, Laub M, Mucheru-Muna MW, Mugendi D, Yegon R, Rasche F, Waswa W, Pulleman M, Vanlauwe B, Six J, Hartmann M. "Can organic amendments override environmental filtering of soil microbiomes? Evidence from 20-year agricultural field trials in contrasting tropical sites" submitted to global change biology 
 &nbsp;

